The presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar failed to deleiver his pooling unit  as President Muhammadu Buhari of the All Progressives Congress. Atiku polled 167 while Buhari recorded 186 at 012 polling unit, Ajiya Ward in Yola where Atiku voted. Meanwhile Buhari defeated Atiku at the Sarkin Yara Ward A, Kofa Baru polling unit (03), Gidan Niyam in Daura local government area of Katsina state. Presiding officer, a corp member, Aliyu Abdullahi announced that Buhari polled 523 votes, while Atiku got 3   Landslide:  Buhari wins own polling unit 2019 Elections: Atiku floors Buhari at Sanwo-Olu's polling unit 2019 elections: Atiku claims Gbenga Daniel’s polling unit